<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Tonle Sap Lake open area in Banteay Meanchey and Siem Reap Provinces, Tonle Sap River in Siem Reap Province and Chhnok Tru landing point, Sangkae River in Battambang Province, Pursat River in Pursat Province, Tang Krasang River in Kampong Thom Province, Sreng River in Siem Reap Province (locality no. 2, 3, 7, 8, 12, 24, 27, 30, 32, 36 and 38); in soft muddy and sandy substrate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morelet" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Scabies" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabies mandarinus" order="Unionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mandarinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scabies mandarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Morelet in 1864, based on specimens collected from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Cochinchina”">&quot;Cochinchina&quot;</normalizedToken>
. This name was previously placed as a junior synonym under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lea" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Scabies" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabies scobinatus" order="Unionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scobinatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scabies scobinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lea, 1856) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1843" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Scabies" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabies crispata" order="Unionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="crispata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scabies crispata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gould, 1843) (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Haas, F" journalOrPublisher="Das Tierreich" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 663" refId="B28" refString="Haas, F, 1969. Superfamilia Unionacea. Das Tierreich 88: 1 - 663" title="Superfamilia Unionacea." volume="88" year="1969">Haas 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brandt, RAM" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 423" refId="B8" refString="Brandt, RAM, 1974. The non-marine aquatic Mollusca of Thailand. Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde 105: 1 - 423" title="The non-marine aquatic Mollusca of Thailand." volume="105" year="1974">Brandt 1974</bibRefCitation>
). Based on molecular phylogeny data, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/mollus/eyy028" author="Pfeiffer, JM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Molluscan Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="403 - 413" refId="B77" refString="Pfeiffer, JM, Graf, DL, Cummings, KS, Page, LM, 2018. Molecular phylogeny and taxonomic revision of two enigmatic freshwater mussel genera (Bivalvia: Unionidae incertae sedis: Harmandia and Unionetta) reveals a diverse clade of Southeast Asian Parreysiinae. Journal of Molluscan Studies 58: 403 - 413, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/mollus/eyy028" title="Molecular phylogeny and taxonomic revision of two enigmatic freshwater mussel genera (Bivalvia: Unionidae incertae sedis: Harmandia and Unionetta) reveals a diverse clade of Southeast Asian Parreysiinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/mollus/eyy028" volume="58" year="2018">Pfeiffer et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
revealed a distinct clade of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1935" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Parreysiinae">Parreysiinae</taxonomicName>
from Mekong delta and eastern gulf of Thailand and resurrected the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morelet" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Scabies" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabies mandarinus" order="Unionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mandarinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scabies mandarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this clade. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeratthitikul, E" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="21 - 36" refId="B33" refString="Jeratthitikul, E, Sutcharit, C, Prasankok, P, 2019a. Molecular phylogeny of the Indochinese freshwater mussel genus Scabies Haas, 1911 (Bivalvia: Unionidae). Tropical Natural History 19 (1): 21 - 36" title="Molecular phylogeny of the Indochinese freshwater mussel genus Scabies Haas, 1911 (Bivalvia: Unionidae)." volume="19" year="2019 a">Jeratthitikul et al. (2019a)</bibRefCitation>
later included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F.Haas" authorityYear="1911" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Scabies" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scabies" order="Unionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scabies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations from the Tonle Sap basin into this species, based on molecular data and shell morphology.
</paragraph>
